text: Hübbe is a surname of Danish or German origin, which is properly Anglicized as Huebbe. Notable people with this surname include: *Edith Agnes Hübbe, born Edith Agnes Cook (1859–1942), pioneering educator in South Australia *Nikolaj Hübbe (born 1967), artistic director of the Royal Danish Ballet *Ulrich Hübbe (1805–1892), German emigrant to South Australia, associated with land titles reform ==References==
title: Hübbe (surname)
